## 3. Invoice Tolerance Rules

### Price Variance Tolerance by Category

| Category | Price Tolerance | Quantity Tolerance | Notes |
|----------|----------------|-------------------|-------|
| Direct materials | +/- 2% | +/- 0% (pay for what arrived) | Price is contract-fixed |
| Indirect / MRO | +/- 5% | +/- 5% | |
| Packaging | +/- 3% | +/- 2% | |
| Services | +/- 0% | N/A | Must match contract exactly |
| Freight | +/- 10% | N/A | Fuel surcharge variability |
| Utilities | +/- 15% | N/A | Tariff variability |

### Escalation Thresholds

- Materiality threshold (auto-approve below): GBP 500
- Category manager escalation: price variance > GBP 5,000
- CPO escalation: price variance > GBP 25,000
- Finance Director escalation: any bank detail change (immediate)

### Fraud Flags (always escalate immediately)

- Bank detail change on any vendor
- Duplicate invoice number from same vendor
- Invoice from vendor not on approved list
- Invoice with no matching PO

---

## 4. Risk Thresholds

### OTD (On-Time Delivery) by Vendor Tier

| Tier | SLA Target | Amber Threshold | Red Threshold | Review Frequency |
|------|-----------|-----------------|---------------|-----------------|
| Tier 1 Strategic | 95% | < 90% | < 85% | Monthly |
| Tier 2 Tactical | 90% | < 85% | < 80% | Quarterly |
| Tier 3 Commodity | 85% | < 80% | < 75% | Annual |
| Tier 4 Bottleneck | 95% | < 90% | < 85% | Quarterly (same as Strategic) |

### Quality Rejection Thresholds

| Category | Acceptable | Amber | Red |
|----------|-----------|-------|-----|
| Direct materials | < 2% | 2-5% | > 5% |
| Indirect materials | < 5% | 5-10% | > 10% |
| Packaging | < 1% | 1-3% | > 3% |

### CPO Hot Alert Triggers (immediate escalation, not weekly brief)

- Any Strategic vendor OTD drops below 75% in a single week
- Any vendor financial distress signal (credit downgrade, CCJ, CVA filing)
- Any Bottleneck vendor delivery failure
- Any bank detail change notification

